title: Charles Lloyd - In The Soviet Union 1967 - Remastered - 320Kbps
description:
Charles Lloyd in the Soviet Union is a live album by jazz saxophonist Charles Lloyd recorded at the International Jazz Festival "Tallinn 1967", Kalevi Sport Hall, Tallinn, Estonia (at that time part of the USSR) in 1967 by the Charles Lloyd Quartet featuring Keith Jarrett, Ron McClure, and Jack DeJohnette.

This well-received festival appearance has four lengthy performances including an 18-minute version of "Sweet Georgia Bright" and Lloyd (who has always had a soft-toned Coltrane influenced tenor style and a more distinctive voice on flute) is in top form . . .


CHARLES  LLOYD

IN  THE  SOVIET  UNION     1967


- CD
- 2005
- Remastered
- 320Kbps


Recorded on May 14, 1967 at Kalevi Sport Hall, Tallinn, Estonia
